	</form></div><span class="pb doctop" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0472">472<a style="padding-left: 5px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0472.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a></span><div class="doc">
      
      <h1>Giuseppe Doria Pamfili<br/>to the American Commissioners</h1>
      <div class="docbody">
        <div class="opener">
          <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Messieurs</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">a Paris le 15. X<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">bre.</span> 1784.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
        </div>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Jai rendu compte  ma Cour de louverture contenue dans La Lettre que Vous mavez fait lhonneur de mcrire le 22. de Septembre dernier.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> Sa Saintet faisant non moins attention  la convenance de Votre proposition, quayant gard  ce que les prrogatives des Catholiques Romains habitans et Sujets des Etats Unis dAmerique, y sont constamment conserves, mordonne de Vous dclarer que tous les batimens portant pavillon des Etats Unis qui aborderont dans les ports de Civitavecchia dans la mditerrane ou dAncone dans lAdriatique y auront tout laccueil quils peuvent desirer; bien entendu que reciproquement les batimens et les effets des Sujets du S<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">t.</span> Siege Seront traits de la mme maniere dans les ports des Etats Unis. A cette dclaration je dois ajouter par ordre exprs de Sa Saintet que les Sujets des Etats Unis dAmrique trouveront dans les ports de la domination du S<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">t.</span> Siege ci-dessus mentionns une personne dpute par Sa Saintet pour leur donner toute lassistence dont ils auront besoin.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Je me flicite dtre charg de Vous dclarer ces intentions de ma Cour qui ne peuvent qutre agrables aux Etats Unis dAmrique.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Jai lhonneur dtre avec une parfaite consideration / Messieurs / Votre trs humble et trs / Obissant Serviteur</p>
        <div class="closer">
          <p class="signed">S.J. Archeveque de Seleucia</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <span class="pb center" title="page number in print edition" id="ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0473">[473<a style="padding-left: 0px" onclick="window.open('/img-document-get.xqy?image=ADMS/Pages/ADMS-06-16/ADMS-06-16-02-pb-0473.jpg', 'pageImage', 'scrollbars=1,resizable=1'); return false" onkeypress="this.onclick();" tabindex="0" title="Click to view image of page from print edition"><img src="/img-ML/page-icon.gif" width="18" height="20" style="vertical-align:middle;" alt="page icon"/></a>]</span>
      <div class="translation">
        <h2>TRANSLATION</h2>
        <div class="opener">
          <table class="salutationBlock">
        <tr>
		<td class="salutationLeft">Gentlemen</td>
		<td class="salutationRight">Paris, 15 December 1784<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0001" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0001-ptr">1</a></td>
	      </tr>
      </table>
        </div>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">I have given an account to my court of the overture contained in the letter that you did me the honor of writing to me on 22 September last.<a class="ptr" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0002" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0002-ptr">2</a> His Holiness, no less mindful of the fitness of your proposal than concerned that the prerogatives of the Roman Catholic inhabitants and subjects of the United States of America are continually preserved, orders me to declare to you that ships under the flag of the United States that land in the ports of Civitavecchia on the Mediterranean or Ancona on the Adriatic will find there all the welcome that they might desire, with the reciprocal understanding, of course, that the ships and goods of the subjects of the Holy See will be treated in the same manner in the ports of the United States. To this declaration I must add by explicit order of His Holiness that the subjects of the United States of America will find in the ports under the dominion of the Holy See mentioned above a person designated by His Holiness to give them all the assistance that they might require.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">I am pleased to be charged with declaring to you the intentions of my court, which can only be agreeable to the United States of America.</p>
        <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">I have the honor of being with perfect respect, gentlemen, your very humble and very obedient servant</p>
        <div class="closer">
          <p class="signed">S.J. Archeveque de Seleucia</p>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="docback">
        <div class="note-source" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-sn">
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;"><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ recipients copy (A recipients copy is assumed to be in the hand of the signer unless it is otherwise described.) ]">RC</abbr> (<span class="ref-terms" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;expan&gt;Papers of the Continental Congress. Originals in the National Archives: Record Group 360. Microfilm edition in 204 reels. Usually cited in the present work from the microfilms, but according to the original series and volume numbering devised in the State Department in the early nineteenth century; for example, PCC, No. 93, III, i.e., the third volume of series 93.&lt;/expan&gt; ]">PCC</span>, No. 86, f. 8588); internal address: [] M<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">rs.</span> Les Ministres Plenipotentiares / [] Etats Unis dAmerique (en Passy); endorsed: Paris Dec<span class="hi-super" style="font-size: 80%; line-height: 0.8; vertical-align: super;">r</span> 15. 1784 / from / The Popes Nuncio; notation: Pope. Some loss of text due to a torn manuscript.</p>

        </div>
        <div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0001-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0001">1</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">Giuseppe Doria Pamfili, the archbishop of Seleucia, served as apostolic nuncio to France from 28 Oct. 1773 to 16 Feb. 1785 (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ Ludwig Bittner and others, eds., &lt;i&gt;Repertorium der diplomatischen Vertreter aller Lnder seit dem Westflischen Frieden (1648),&lt;/i&gt; Oldenburg, 19361965; 3 vols. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Repertorium,</span></span> 3:291). Although dated 15 Dec. 1784, this letter was not delivered to the commissioners until late Feb. 1785 (<a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0333" class="document">commissioners to John Jay, 18 March</a>, below).</p>

        </div>

        <div class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0002-ptr" id="ADMS-06-16-02-0275-fn-0002">2</a>
          
   <p style="text-indent: 1.5em; text-align: left;">See the commissioners <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0208" class="document">9 Sept. 1784</a> letter to the Baron von Thulemeier, and <a href="default.xqy?keys=ADMS-print-06-16-02-0208&amp;expandNote=ADMS-06-16-02-0208-fn-0003#ADMS-06-16-02-0208-fn-0003" class="document">note 3</a>, above.</p>

        </div>

      </div>
